Project: Nibras - AI Grading System
Stack: TypeScript, Node.js, Fastify, Next.js, Prisma, OpenAI

Coding Standards:
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Use async/await for all async operations
- Always handle errors with try-catch
- Use Zod for schema validation
- Export types and functions from index.ts files

AI Grading Guidelines:
- Use structured outputs (JSON Schema) for all AI calls
- Temperature: 0.1-0.2 for consistent grading
- Confidence threshold: 0.8 (flag below for human review)
- Always include model answer when available
- Store full AI response for auditability

File Structure:
- Prompts: packages/grading/src/prompts/
- Services: packages/grading/src/services/
- Types: packages/grading/src/types.ts
- Utils: packages/grading/src/utils/
